MultipleChoiceQuestion.text:
Which of the following Scratch instructions do the same thing?

\begin{itemize}
 \item[1:] \code{change belugaBeetle by 2}
 \item[2:] \code{set belugaBeetle to belugaBeetle + belugaBeetle}
 \item[3:] \code{set belugaBeetle to 1 + belugaBeetle + 1}
\end{itemize}

Which of the following Scratch compound instructions do the same thing?

\begin{itemize}
 \item[1:] \code{if doberman = 0\\
 \codeIndent say \fbox{That's a dog!}}
 \item[2:] \code{if doberman = 0\\
 \codeIndent say \fbox{That's a dog!}\\
 else\\
 \codeIndent wait 1 sec}
 \item[3:] \code{if doberman = 0\\
 \codeIndent say \fbox{That's a dog!}\\
 else}
\end{itemize}

Mary wants to write a piece of a Scratch script to determine whether the number value stored in variable \code{antelope} is greater than 10.  Which of the following code snippets could she use to do this?

\begin{itemize}
 \item[1:] \code{if antelope > 10\\
 \codeIndent say \fbox{antelope is greater than 10}\\
 else\\
 \codeIndent say \fbox{antelope is not greater than 10}}
 \item[2:] \code{if antelope > 10\\
 \codeIndent say \fbox{antelope is greater than 10}\\
 say \fbox{antelope is not greater than 10}}
\end{itemize}

MultipleChoiceQuestion.choice:
\begin{tabular}{llll}
    A & B \phantom{a} & C & D \\
    E & F \phantom{a} & G & H 
\end{tabular}

\begin{tabular}{llll}
    A & C \phantom{a} & E & G \\
    B & D \phantom{a} & F & H 
\end{tabular}

MultipleChoiceQuestion.answer:
\begin{tabular}{llll}
    A & B \phantom{a} & E & F \\
    C & D \phantom{a} & G & H 
\end{tabular}
